            <h3>Angeles City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Take a heritage and historical tour. At the center of Sto. Heritage District is the Holy Rosary Parish Church, Angeles City’s most famous landmark. Kapampangans are a proud group and one can learn more about them at the Center for Kapampangan Studies at Holy Angel University. Visit the Museo ning Angeles housed at the old municipio building and find out how Angeles City came to be -- from its beginnings, the aftermath of the eruption of Mt. Pinatubo to the makings of an emerging cosmopolitan city. A guided package tour can be arranged at the Museo ning Angeles.</li>
                <li>2. Eat Kapampangan. Angeles City is located in Pampanga, known as the Culinary Capital of the Philippines. The City is the birthplace of the sizzling sisig. For the adventurous, try famous exoticas such as betute, frogs stuffed with ground pork meat and local herbs, and camaru (mole crickets) cooked dry adobo-style.</li>
                <li>3. Indulge in international cuisine in the City’s gastronomic belt. Spoil yourself on a staggering array of international restau- rants in the city’s entertainment center. Stretching from the Balibago Strip to Fields District, Don Juico Avenue and all the way to Fil-Am Friendship Highway just outside Clark Freeport Zone, Angeles City’s gastronomic belt is home to the best of world cuisine. A melting pot of culinary cultures, Angeles City is also the birthplace of Panizza, a thin-crust panini cum pizza rolled with arugula and alfalfa sprouts. This culinary invention by a Swiss national turned Angeleno has been making waves in the national scene and replicated in many restaurants in and out of the city.</li>
                <li>4. Pamper yourself at the Puning Hot Springs. Enjoy a healing trip at Angeles City’s nature’s spa located in Barangay Sapang Bato complete with beauty treatments, lunch, a round trip 4x4 ride from the Garden Restaurant to the hot springs, use of facilities, sand steam where you will be covered up to your neck with volcanic sand, body mud pack, and a foot massage. One attraction is a steaming hot waterfall.</li>
                <li>5. Bask in the glow of city night life. Chill out and enjoy the laidback atmosphere at the Balibago’s entertainment district. Enjoy live weekend music with your date, friends or family at Cioccolo Bistro, located within the plush Grand Palazzo Royale Estate. There are over a hundred night establishments in Angeles City – many are within walking or short driving distance from each other. Activities range from the international standard night clubs, Japanese and Chinese-style karaoke bars, to hi- tech discothèques. Feeling lucky? Your fortune could just turn for the better inside the Casino Filipino Angeles along McArthur Highway in Balibago, just outside of Clark.</li>
            </ol>

