            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>Angeles City is located at the heart of the Pampanga province in Central Luzon.
                From Manila, it is 83 kilometers, a 45-minute drive via the North Luzon Expressway. Motorists coming from Metro Manila are advised to exit at the Angeles – Magalang toll plaza to proceed to the City proper.
                The Diosdado Macapagal International Airport offers regular flights to Manila and Caticlan via Seair, Inc. and Cebu via Cebu Pacific. International flights to Malaysia (Kuala Lumpur and Kota Kinabalu), Singapore, Macau, Thailand (Bangkok), Taiwan (Taipei) Hong Kong and South Korea are also available.</p>

            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <p>1. Angeles City is a year-round destination but the celebration of its twin fiesta in October offers a host of exciting activities ranging from cultural, culinary, community and sports events.</p>

